column1: ConditionsEvent/Operation:Aerial Strand and Cable PlacementPermit Linear Footage16000Elements of OccupancyMoving pole to pole along the street placing aerialstrand and cable.  Will not be at a pole longer than 30minutes.From:1/11/2016 07:00AMStart Time7:00AMTo:1/22/2016 05:00PMEnd Time05:00PMNeed to call for InspectionNeed to post tow-away signTo activate and register this permit for towing, call(415) 554-5824 a minimum of 72 hours prior tooccupancy.  To tow a vehicle call the Tow Desk at(415) 553-1200.Special Traffic permit requiredCALL FOR Special traffic permit MAY BE required(Please check DPT Blue Book for any trafficrestrictions; to obtain a "Blue Book", please contactMTA at (415) 701-4673).Food:NOther:Performing Arts:NStreet Space Hours7:00AM Thru 05:00PMMeter Segment(s)Night Noise

Prior to construction, all CCSFsurvey monuments shall bereferenced by a licensed LandSurveyor on a Corner Record ora Record of Survey if anyconstruction will take placewithin 10 ft of a monument. Forany questions, please emailMonument.Preservation@sfdpw.org or call 415-554-5827.Note, all survey monumentsshall be preserved per state lawand disturbance of a surveymonument may be a crime.
